<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911023-0004</DOCNO><DOCID>911023-0004.</DOCID><HL>   International:   Toshiba Machine Co.</HL><DATE>10/23/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10</SO><CO>   J.TSB</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)INTERNATIONAL TRADE NEWS (TRD)</IN><NS>TRADE ISSUES (TRD)</NS><RE>FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   TOKYO -- Toshiba Machine Co. of Japan said it plans tore-enter the U.S. machine tools market &quot;little by little&quot;after a three-year ban on exports of its tools to the U.S.expires at the end of December.   The U.S. government suspended sales of Toshiba tools in1987 after it was discovered the company had violated rulesset by the Coordinating Committee for Export Control, orCocom, by selling sophisticated propeller machinery to theSoviet Union.</LP><TEXT>   The company will begin responding to customer requests inJanuary, and hopes to slowly recover U.S. sales through theservice arm of its U.S. unit, a company official said. Thesubsidiary was allowed to maintain its after-sales operationsdespite the ban on new sales.</TEXT></DOC>